title: GMC Sierra 2500hd Duramax

body:
QR Code Link to This Post


Body: Over all the truck has 179K that is on the body and axles, has a 2 inch cowl hood, 50 inch curved led light bar, low rise tool box in the bed, gmc front gill with billet insert.
Interior: Cloth seats, buckets in the front with center console bench in rear, pioneer cd player with pioneer door speakers, cluster and hvac control head have blue led lights, driver seat does have a medium side tear in the cloth.
Power train: here is where the big changes are, the engine, trans, and t-case, drive shafts, exhaust all have just 500 miles on them.
Engine: 6.2L (376 ci) started life as a 6.0L LQ4 I rebuilt the engine it was bored out to a 4.065 bore that makes it a 6.2L done by PPE, it has new rods, pistons, ring, bearing, melling high pressure oil pump, LS2 HD timing set, LS7 lifters, hardened push rods, beehive springs, small comp cam, heads (317) received a full valve job and mill, texas speed long tube headers, custom true duals with X pipe and 40 series flows, s&b cold air, new starter, alternator, water pump, power steering pump, gear box, all new hoses
Transmission: 4L80E, fully rebuilt all new clutches and seals, triple disk converter, dual coolers mounted up front, new drive shafts front and rear (A&I) 
Transfer Case: stock rebuild manual shift
Suspension: truck has had full front end rebuild 2 years ago, 2 inch body lift, 2 inch suspension lift, cooper stt 35x12.5 r15`s i also have a 5th tire never ran
this is a awesome running truck not another one like it around she is 22 years old so yes there are some dents and scratches and a little clear coat damage but still cleans up very nice, i am asking $7,900.00 o.b.r.o. NO PAYMENTS, and not looking to trade for your project .pm for any other questions.
